07/03/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Police in Tirana announced on Sunday (March 6th) the arrests of two people believed to have been involved in the illegal production of homemade explosives for years. 
Artan Hasani, 38, and Endri Hametaj, 28, were detained on one of the main roads in the capital. 
They are the suspected leaders of a gang whose explosives were used in several bombings over the past year. 
(Balkan Web, Top Channel, Klan - 06/03/11)
